kazimierz aleksander gzowski (october 8, 1901 in sumy near kharkiv, russian empire â€“ june 25, 1986 in london, great britain) was a polish cavalry officer and horse rider who competed in the 1928 summer olympics. he won the silver medal with the polish team in the team jumping with his horse mylord after finishing fourth in the individual jumping. gzowski fought in world war ii with the polish forces in the west. after the war, he stayed in england.